SIMPLE: goody-goody
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Goody-goody
<hw>Good"y-good`y</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Mawkishly or weakly good;
exhibiting goodness with silliness.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>goody-goody</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: goody-goody
<hw>good"y-good"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person who is
weakly, sentimentally, or affectedly good; a goody-goody person; --
sometimes used to refer to person who acts with good intentions but who
bunglingly does more harm than good. The latter may sometimes be
deprecatingly referred to as a <altname>goo-goo</altname>.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Goodyship</ent>⟦br⟧
